10/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- New Parliament Speaker Mehmet Ali Sahin took over the post Sunday (August 9th) from Koksal Toptan, whose mandate expired.
Sahin, a lawyer, went to high school with Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan.
Eight years ago, he co-founded -- along with Erdogan and President Abdullah Gul -- the ruling Justice and Development Party.
Between 2002 and 2007 he served as deputy prime minister and justice minister.
(BTA, Anadolu news agency - 09/08/09)
